12:
University GPA Calculation System
Scenario
A university calculates GPA using marks of 5 subjects:
Average ≥ 85 → Distinction
Average ≥ 70 → First Class
Average ≥ 50 → Second Class
Else → Fail
Question
Write an R function to calculate GPA classification.
Answer
calculate_gpa <- function(marks){
avg <- mean(marks)
if(avg >= 85){
result <- "Distinction"
} else if(avg >= 70){
result <- "First Class"
} else if(avg >= 50){
result <- "Second Class"
} else {
result <- "Fail"
}
return(result)
}
calculate_gpa(c(78, 85, 90, 72, 80))
 
 
Question
13:
Smart Electricity Meter System
Scenario
A smart meter calculates bill based on peak and off-peak usage:
Peak units → ₹6/unit
Off-peak units → ₹3/unit
10% surcharge if total units > 300
 
Question
Write an R function to calculate electricity bill.
Answer
smart_meter_bill <- function(peak_units, offpeak_units){
bill <- (peak_units * 6) + (offpeak_units * 3)
total_units <- peak_units + offpeak_units
 
if(total_units > 300){
bill <- bill * 1.10
}
return(bill)
}
smart_meter_bill(180, 150)
